positions.description:
* Researches, designs, implements and maintains the operation of Linux servers in Clustered and Virtualized environments in support of the business;
* Evaluates vendor products in hardware and software and recommends purchases consistent with organizational standards;
* Provides routine system administration support such as installation and configuration of application services, server monitoring, system backups as well as incident, change and configuration management;
* Seeks out opportunities for continuous improvements, automation and cost reduction;
* Deploys and integrates technologies such as RHCS, KVM and XEN Virtualization, SAN allocation, Apache, Tomcat, MySql, Likewise, Puppet, Cobbler and Postfix.

* Supported Planet Discovers' Entire 350+ Linux server farm (40 clusters, 80% XEN instances) for search engine product that handles over 2 million hits per day;
* Served as member of a team responsible for all aspects of IT department from server management to planning, building, deployment, administration (including 24x7 on call support) and security;
* Automated several large portions of provisioning of new customer sites and user accounts to increase productivity and decrease errors;
* Designed and implemented a solution which provides on-site and off-site backups of all servers;
* Installed and configured 350+ new Linux servers running Tomcat, Apache, MySql, Postfix, BIND, MRTG, Hobbit  on Dell PowerEdge 2950 and R710 hardware;
* Installed and configured 350+ systems using Xen virtualization;
* Setup Red Hat Kickstart environment with PXE booting for building new servers and clusters;
* Setup daily monitoring of servers with Hobbit/Big Brother;
* Deployed centralized logging solution with syslog-ng over stunnel and Splunk for indexing;
* Built a Nessus server “vulnerability assessment tool” to scan the Linux servers and network devices for vulnerabilities on a biweekly bases;
* Built VPN connections between the different  datacenters using Cisco PIX and openVPN;
* Administered the company email server Zimbra;
* Coordinated and implemented large scale datacenter migration of over 350 servers;
* Centralized users login using openLDAP, MySQL and PAM;

* Migrated servers running Windows to Red Hat and Slackware;
* Installed and configured Linux servers running BIND, Sendmaill, Qpopper, Tomcat, Apache, LDAP,  DHCP, MySQL, SpamAssassin, MRTG, Nessus, iptables;
* Setup Red Hat Kickstart and PXE remote installation environment;
* Setup an imaging environment using SystemImager;
* Deployed a high available cluster with LVS and Heartbeat;
* Installed an extensive Network Intrusion Detection System using Snort and ACID across the enterprise;
* Built a VPN connectivity with openVPN;
* Build Linux/MySQL/J2EE based in-house software system for the business;

* Installed and managed Slackware Linux Farm in a production, QA, and development environment;
* Installed and configured DNS, Sendmail, Tomcat, Apache, LDAP,  DHCP, MySql and iptables
* Trained the employees; Wrote a system restoration manual;
* Installed network appliances such as Cisco Routers and Switches;

